org.jtrim.concurrent

Class DoneFuture<ResultType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jtrim.concurrent.DoneFuture<ResultType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ResultType - the type of the result of this future
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Future<ResultType>

    public final class DoneFuture<ResultType>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.concurrent.Future<ResultType>
    Defines a future of an already done task. No underlying task is actually necessary, only the result of the (possibly not existent) task. This future is not cancelable, attempting to cancel it does nothing.

    Thread safety

    Methods of this class are safe to use by multiple threads concurrently.

    Synchronization transparency

    The methods of this class are synchronization transparent.
